User Interface - TM1638 LED&KEY 
LED Functions : 
LED1 = 		Control & Motor ENABLED 
LED2 = 		Division Mode 
LED3 = 		Angle Mode 
LED4 = 		Rotation Mode, Flashing (0.5 Sec) 
LED5 = 		ON = CCW 
LED6 = 		ON = Divisions (S6) 
LED7 = 		ON = Position achieved 
LED8 = 		ON = Motor Locked 


Buttons Functions : 
S1 		TOGGLE OFF/ON	//Hold for 2 sec 
OFF = Disables Motor	(OR System Failure)
All LEDs OFF, Maintain Display indicating command # requested 
ON = Enable Motor, LED1 back on, Other LEDs Resume previous State, 
Status digits back to normal operation. 

S2 		SETUP (Default) =Division Mode (LED 2 = ON)
TOGGLE =Angle Mode (LED 3 = ON) //Hold for 3 sec
TOGGLE =Rotation Mode(LED 4 = ON) //Hold for 3 sec
TOGGLE =Back to Division Mode (LED 2 = ON) //Hold for 3 sec
S3 		TOGGLE = Motor OFF, TOGGLE = RESET Digits to “0”, Motor ON //Hold for 3 sec

S4 		MEMORIZE RPM  //Hold for 1 sec

S5 		TOGGLE CW/CCW //Hold for 3 sec

S6 		TOGGLE for WHOLE or DIVISIONS //Hold for 1 sec

S7 		Raise Command Numbers (Hold 1 sec for 5 increments/sec) 
					(Hold 6 sec more for 20 increments/sec)

S8 		Lower Command Numbers (Hold 1 sec for 5 increments/sec)
					(Hold 6 sec more for 20 increments/sec)

SW1 (External) 	In Divisions Mode = START/NEXT //Hold for 3 sec
In Angles Mode = START/NEXT //Hold for 3 sec
In Rotation Mode = JOG 	//Hold for 1 sec,
   Start	//Hold 10 Sec,
   Stop	//Hold 200Ms	 

3 Modes: Divisions, Angles, Rotation. 

Divisions MODE: 0/400 1 by 1 (3 Digits) (LED2 =ON)
Digit 2, 3, 4. (Select S7+, S8-) 

Angle Mode: 360 Deg. (6 Digits) (LED3 =On) 
Precision: 1.000 (+- 0.001)
Digit 2, 3, 4. 5, 6, 7 (Select S7+, S8-) 
TOGGLE S6 = Whole # <Digit 2, 3, 4 
TOGGLE S6 = Divisions # >Digit 5, 6, 7 (LED6=ON)

Rotation Mode: 360 Deg. 1 by 1 (6 Digits) (LED4=ON, Flashing Cont. 0.5 Sec) 
Digit 2, 3, 4. = Angle from "0" 
Digit 5, 6, 7. = Motor Output RPM (Speed Ajust (Select S7+ S8-)(Hold for FAST INCREMENT)) 

Max Speed determined in C++ code, 1 to 500 RPM max (motiom.cpp) 

Soft accelaration/decelaration on all functions 

Lock Motor on STOP 

Anti bounce (200 min) on all buttons S1>S8, including SW1 (External) (C++ Programming)

The complete setup will be used exclusively for that machine, no other input or SD card.

